abstract: NEW-YORK, Saturday, March 31 -- P.M. While there was undoubtedly considerable profit taking to-day, the market readily absorbed all offerings without showing signs of weakness. This was due mainly to the tree buying, not only for the foreign account, but for that of local investors. The prevailing sentiment was decidedly hopeful at the close of business.

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, April 6 -- The best pigeon-flying speed of the season was made yesterday in a journey against time from Odenton, Md., to the Charles Mehler loft in West Philadelphia. abstract: NEW-YORK, Saturday, April 7 -- P.M. The taking of profits, both for foreign and domestic accounts, gave a reactionary appearance to to-day's stock market. abstract: CHICAGO, April 9 -- The reaction predicted in the stock market, which was expected for several days by all but the most rabid bulls, showed itself to-day. It appeared shortly after the opening, especially on West Chicago. For a time all the offerings at 157 were taken, but gradually the orders were filled, and prices broke to 156, recovering again to 156 1/2, and closing firm at 156 3/4.

abstract: CHICAGO, April 10 -- A belief that the Government report would not be a bullish one on wheat had many advocates on the floor to-day. An easier market resulted from selling on this theory. Just why this impression became popular cannot be satisfactorily explained. Some said that a compilation of statistics by a private crop-reporting concern composed of ex-employes of ex-Statician Dodge were responsible for the premature report.

abstract: WHITE PLAINS, N.Y., April 17. -- The regular Spring meeting of the Presbytery of Westchester, which embraces the Counties of Westchester, Putnam, and the State of Connecticut, began this afternoon in the Presbyterian Church here, and is attended by about fifty pastors and Elders. The Rev. Alexander Miller of Mahopac Falls, the retiring Moderator, delivered the sermon.

abstract: NEW-HAVEN, Conn., April 24 -- Business in local manufactories continues to improve. Yesterday morning L. abstract: Chief of Police Eustace of Gravesend will undertake a gigantic job to-day, one that John Y. abstract: Winchester, Va., April 29. -- The greater part of the best business block in town was burned today by a fire of incendiary origin. The total loss is $80,000.
